     </div>
     <div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA04d089n2-ptr" id="PJA04d089n2">2</a>
      
   <p>Col. Thomas Marshall (<span class="ref-st" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ &lt;i&gt;Journals of the House of Representatives of Massachusetts&lt;/i&gt; [[1715-]], Boston, reprinted by the Massachusetts Historical Society, 1919-. (For the years for which reprints are not yet available, the original printings are cited, by year and session.) ]">Mass., <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">House Jour.</span></span>, 17751776, 4th sess., p. 221).</p>

     </div>
     <div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA04d089n3-ptr" id="PJA04d089n3">3</a>
      
   <p>On 25 April, Warren was appointed to the Superior Court as a substitute for one of those who had declined (Records of the States, Microfilm, Mass. E.1, Reel No. 9, Unit 2, p. 122; William Cushing to <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Adams (17351826) ]">JA</abbr>, <a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-06-04-02-0086" class="document">20 May</a>, below).</p>

     </div>
     <div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA04d089n4-ptr" id="PJA04d089n4">4</a>
      
   <p>Joseph Hawley.</p>

     </div>
     <div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA04d089n5-ptr" id="PJA04d089n5">5</a>
      
   <p><span class="ref-st" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ &lt;i&gt;The Acts and Resolves, Public and Private, of the Province of the Massachusetts Bay&lt;/i&gt;, Boston, 18691922; 21 vols. ]">Mass., <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Province Laws</span></span>, 5:502503.</p>

     </div>
     <div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA04d089n6-ptr" id="PJA04d089n6">6</a>
      
